of conversation
about what his wife said in her
speech last

28:00.345 --> 28:05.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
night and whether there was any
similarity
with the speech given by
Michelle Obama in

28:05.717 --> 28:07.252 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
2008.

28:07.352 --> 28:11.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
David, is this something that is
going to
put a blemish on the whole
affair?

28:11.690 --> 28:15.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes, I think so.
It was plagiarism.
I thought it was pretty clear.

28:15.460 --> 28:20.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it says a couple things.
First, the
staff is not that good. This is
an outsider

28:20.365 --> 28:24.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
campaign. They haven't hired the
best people,
the professionals, and so that
showed. Whoever

28:24.102 --> 28:28.707 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
did it, it was a big mess-up
that no professional
would do.

28:28.807 --> 28:33.312 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Second, they couldn't admit it.
They couldn't
just say, OK, we messed up,
we're firing somebody,

28:33.412 --> 28:36.882 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we admit it, we're moving on,
because that's
not Donald Trump's persona.

28:36.982 --> 28:41.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, third, I have a feeling
that the shoe
is yet to drop, that somewhere
in this country,

28:41.853 --> 28:45.157 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump is sitting there,
wanting to
defend his wife's honor, wanting
-- getting

28:45.257 --> 28:49.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mad because people are attacking
his family,
and, somehow, he is going to
riff on this.

28:49.995 --> 28:53.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it might be Thursday night
in the hall
or it might be somewhere else,
but there will

28:53.532 --> 28:56.368 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be another little mini-bomb,
when Donald Trump
reacts.

28:56.468 --> 28:59.571 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Late last night, we
were sitting
around here at this table and we
were talking

28:59.671 --> 29:03.108 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about missed opportunities on
the opening
day of the convention.

29:03.208 --> 29:04.276 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Is this another one, Amy?

29:04.376 --> 29:06.211 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AMY WALTER, The Cook Political
Report: Absolutely.

29:06.311 --> 29:11.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we talked yesterday about
the unity, and
we were talking to Lisa
Desjardins right now

29:11.416 --> 29:13.151 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
